reasoning='To implement a 5-transistor single-ended OTA with a bias current port (“ibp10u”) and differential inputs (vin, vip), I chose a classic NMOS differential pair (M3/M4) with an NMOS tail-current source (M5) and a PMOS current-mirror active load (M1/M2). The diode-connected PMOS M1 at the drain of M3 sets the mirror gate, and M2 mirrors that current into the vip/M4 branch, producing a single-ended output at vout. This requires exactly five transistors. The netlist uses the foundry’s tsmc18dN and tsmc18dP models and keeps all pin names in the subckt declaration. The top-level instance (“I16 … ota”) is preserved exactly per the template. No placeholders remain.' config=ConfigFile(netlist='// Library name: MP3
// Cell name: ota
// View name: schematic
subckt ota VDD VSS ibp10u vin vip vout
    M5 (ns ibp10u VSS VSS) tsmc18dN w=10u l=0.18u
    M3 (nd3 vin ns VSS) tsmc18dN w=10u l=0.18u
    M4 (nd4 vip ns VSS) tsmc18dN w=10u l=0.18u
    M1 (nd3 nd3 VDD VDD) tsmc18dP w=20u l=0.18u
    M2 (vout nd3 VDD VDD) tsmc18dP w=20u l=0.18u
ends ota
// Library name: MP3
// Cell name: dut
// View name: schematic
I16 (net1 net2 net6 net4 net3 net5) ota')
